n. Wheeler Scores Prosperity Con\nferences on Unemployment\nSen.\nWheeler (D., Mont.) today\nintroduced into the Record an edi\ntorial on unemployment appearing\nin yesterday\u2019s edition of The News.\nWheeler charged that the \u201cpros\nperity conferences\" at the White\nHouse last fall, attended by busi\nne:\nleaders of the country, con\ntributed to the unemployment of the\nnation by \u201cscaring\u201d the employers\ninto believing that there was a real\nbusiness depression in the country.\nCarter\u2019s Residence\nUnder Police Guard\nFollowing Threats\nLittle Disposition Seen to\nInvestigate Enforcement\nLaxity Charges of Printer\nThe residence of Public Printer\nGoorge H. Carter, at 1661 Hobart\nst nw, has been placed under police\nobservation and a detective rides\nwith him in his auto from his office,\nfollowing a series of threats from\n\"gunmen\" against Carter\u2019s life,\nj Carter said he received another\nthreat today\u2014the third in two days\n\u2014from a \"notorious gambler.\" Word\nsent was that it would \"be easy to\nimport a gunman to get you for\n$5000.\"\nThe threats are the result of Car\nter\u2019s attack against gambling in the\nvieinity of the Government Printing\nOffice.\nRow May End\nThe row now on between Police\nChief Pratt and Carter probably will\nend where it started.\nThere is little disposition on the\npart of the investigating subcom\nmittee of the Senate to pry into the\nmatter. The subcommittee is headed\nby Sen. Robsion (R., Ky.), who is\nfirmly opposed to making the sub\ncommittee a \u201csewer thru which a\nfilth of character-besmirching testi\nmony might pass.\u201d\nWill Examine Evidence\nRobsion plans to examine the evi\ndence of \u201ccorruption or stupidity,\u201d\ncharged by Carter against the police\nforce, but his predisposition is to\nsteer the subcommittee clear from\nany interference with what he re\ngards as a function intended for the\ni grand jury.\nSen. Blease, who yesterday gave\n\u201clip service\u201d to Carter\u2019s charges,\nwhich are quite similar to the\ncharges the South Carolinan has\nmade frequently in recent months,\nis a member of the subcommittee\nbut he is not pressing for any ac\ntion.\nBlease likes to have his say\nfrom the Senate floor every once in\nawhile and let it go at that.\n\u201cIf possible to avoid it,\u201d Robsion\nsaid to newspaper men, \u201cthis sub\ncommittee should never usurp any\nauthority already delegated.\n\"I'm going to call the matter be\ni fore the subcommittee and see what\na majority think, but offhand it ap\ni pears to me that charges such as\nCarter is reported to have made\nshould be placed properly before the\nDistrict Attorney and grand jury.\nIf they fail to function, then it is\na matter for the subcommittee to\ninvestigate them,\ncharges.\u201d\nand not\nthe\nMany Issues Lower\nat Profit-Taking\nOthers Creep Up on Demand\nin Moderate Turnover; Steel\nIs Off Slightly\nBy United Press\nNEW YORK Week-end proft\ntaking brought down many issues in\nthe opening dealings on the stock ex\nchange today. The majority, how\never, were slightly above previous\nclosing levels in moderate turnover.\nAtchison declined 1% to 230, Beth\nlehem Steel to 100, Chrysler\nto 3S12, Gillette 18 to 96%, ai\nGeneral Motors\nSteel opened off\nshares.\nto 423s\n\n\nU.\nat 13212 on 10\nAmerican Telephone Telegraph\ncontinued in demand, rising nearly a\npoint to 2413, while smaller, gains\nwere made by American Smelting,\nKennecott, International Nickel, and\nGeneral Electric.\nD.H.Lawrence Near Death\nNICE, France\u2014Doctors forbade\nthe removal of D. II. Lawrence, nov\nelist, to Arizona yesterday, saying\nhis condition was hopeless. Jo Da\nvidson, American sculptor, sat at\nthe sick man\u2019s bedside and modeled\nhis head.\nAMOCO-gAS\nAlways lowest\ncost per mile\nNow lower\nthan\never\nA\nf AMERICAN OIL COMPANY\nAf\nh Psa Amerksn Petroleum at Traasport Company\nGeneral Ofa Belumore. Md\n\nLowcost\nI mile is what y\nA counts./","height":"21832","width":"14428"}}
